        "authorId" : "9b5a6de7-1648-432f-a400-7a47bea935d8",
        "body" : "If you have two characters in the Ahem font at size 15, then the dimensions will be exactly 30x15, with the baseline at exactly 12 pixels from the top.\r\n\r\n(This only works if the characters are in the Ahem font's character set, which covers most ASCII characters including in particular A-Z, a-z, 0-9, and space.)\r\n\r\nIn addition, the space character will be drawn as a transparent square, the Ã‰ character will be drawn as fill above the baseline and transparent below, the p character will be drawn as transparent above the baseline and filled below, and the other characters will be drawn as filled squares.",
